1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. f4 d6 6. Nf3 Bg4 7. Na4 { We want to get rid of this bishop immediately. Black has some counterplay: taking our N on f3, then Nd4, forcing our Q back, then b5 forking us! } 7... Bb6 (7... Bxf3 8. Qxf3 Nd4 9. Qd1 b5 (9... exf4) 10. Bxf7+ Kxf7 11. Nxc5 dxc5 12. fxe5 Nd7 13. c3) 8. Nxb6 axb6 9. c3 (9. a3 Nd4 10. fxe5 dxe5 11. Bxf7+ Kxf7 12. Nxe5+) (9. O-O exf4 (9... Nd4 10. fxe5 dxe5)) 9... O-O 10. O-O h6 11. h3 Bxf3 { he kinda had to } (11... Bh5 12. g4 Bg6 13. f5) 12. Qxf3 exf4 13. Bxf4 Na5 14. Bb5 c6 15. Ba4 Nc4 16. Bb3 Nd2?? 17. Bxd2 d5 (17... Nh7) 18. Bxh6 gxh6 19. Qxf6 Qxf6 20. Rxf6 *


